      "score": 38,
      "comments": 6,
      "author": "b--man",
      "published": "2026-07-22T21:33:12Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Language selection dictates memory safety and type systems, directly impacting CVE prevalence, runtime stability, and compile-time bug prevention.",
        "Language runtimes dictate performance ceilings, memory overhead, and concurrency models, balancing garbage collection pauses against low-level resource control.",
        "Ecosystem maturity, compiler diagnostics, and package management significantly govern long-term code maintainability, refactoring safety, and engineering velocity."
      ]
    },
